# =============================================================================
# Render redirect map — Torin Gunnell Digital  (CLAUDE.md §3.2, §9)
# =============================================================================
# Format:  /old-path   /new-path   301
#
# CRITICAL: before cutover, inventory the current Wix site's ranking URLs from
# Google Search Console. Every old URL that ranks MUST resolve on the new site —
# either it exists at the same path, or it 301-redirects here. An old ranking URL
# that returns 404 is the one thing that actually kills rankings.
#
# Clean folder URLs (/contact/, /wedding-films/, etc.) are served automatically
# by Render from each folder's index.html — those don't need an entry here.
#
# Mappings below are built from the live Wix page inventory (SEO Settings →
# Main Pages). Old Wix paths used no trailing slash; the new site serves folder
# URLs with a trailing slash.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Old Wix path           New path                301
/wedding-videography     /wedding-films/         301
/about-me                /who-we-are/            301
/allthethings            /all-the-things/        301
/search                  /                       301
/blog                    /                        301

# Same-topic page kept at the SAME URL on the new site (no redirect needed):
#   /wedding-photography  → served by /wedding-photography/index.html
#   /contact              → served by /contact/index.html
#   /                     → served by /index.html
